metadata.name: Confirmation already confirmed user should not be able to confirm the account again

children.name: password=
children.comment:
# Generates a hashed password based on the given value.
# For legacy reasons, we use `encrypted_password` to store
# the hashed password.

children.name: password_digest
children.comment:
# Hashes the password using bcrypt. Custom hash functions should override
# this method to apply their own algorithm.
#
# See https://github.com/heartcombo/devise-encryptable for examples
# of other hashing engines.

children.name: send_devise_notification
children.comment:
# This is an internal method called every time Devise needs
# to send a notification/mail. This can be overridden if you
# need to customize the e-mail delivery logic. For instance,
# if you are using a queue to deliver e-mails (active job, delayed
# job, sidekiq, resque, etc), you must add the delivery to the queue
# just after the transaction was committed. To achieve this,
# you can override send_devise_notification to store the
# deliveries until the after_commit callback is triggered.
#
# The following example uses Active Job's `deliver_later` :
#
#     class User
#       devise :database_authenticatable, :confirmable
#
#       after_commit :send_pending_devise_notifications
#
#       protected
#
#       def send_devise_notification(notification, *args)
#         # If the record is new or changed then delay the
#         # delivery until the after_commit callback otherwise
#         # send now because after_commit will not be called.
#         # For Rails < 6 use `changed?` instead of `saved_changes?`.
#         if new_record? || saved_changes?
#           pending_devise_notifications << [notification, args]
#         else
#           render_and_send_devise_message(notification, *args)
#         end
#       end
#
#       private
#
#       def send_pending_devise_notifications
#         pending_devise_notifications.each do |notification, args|
#           render_and_send_devise_message(notification, *args)
#         end
#
#         # Empty the pending notifications array because the
#         # after_commit hook can be called multiple times which
#         # could cause multiple emails to be sent.
#         pending_devise_notifications.clear
#       end
#
#       def pending_devise_notifications
#         @pending_devise_notifications ||= []
#       end
#
#       def render_and_send_devise_message(notification, *args)
#         message = devise_mailer.send(notification, self, *args)
#
#         # Deliver later with Active Job's `deliver_later`
#         if message.respond_to?(:deliver_later)
#           message.deliver_later
#         # Remove once we move to Rails 4.2+ only, as `deliver` is deprecated.
#         elsif message.respond_to?(:deliver_now)
#           message.deliver_now
#         else
#           message.deliver
#         end
#       end
#
#     end
#

children.name: password_required?
children.comment:
# Checks whether a password is needed or not. For validations only.
# Passwords are always required if it's a new record, or if the password
# or confirmation are being set somewhere.

children.name: confirmation_required?
children.comment: # Callback to overwrite if confirmation is required or not.

children.name: confirmed?
children.comment: # Verifies whether a user is confirmed or not

children.name: generate_confirmation_token
children.comment:
# Generates a new random token for confirmation, and stores
# the time this token is being generated in confirmation_sent_at

children.name: skip_reconfirmation_in_callback!
children.comment:
# To not require reconfirmation after creating with #save called in a
# callback call skip_create_confirmation!

children.name: send_on_create_confirmation_instructions
children.comment:
# A callback method used to deliver confirmation
# instructions on creation. This can be overridden
# in models to map to a nice sign up e-mail.

children.name: send_confirmation_instructions
children.comment: # Send confirmation instructions by email

children.name: send_email_changed_notification?
children.comment:
# With reconfirmable, notify the original email when the user first
# requests the email change, instead of when the change is confirmed.

children.name: confirm_by_token
children.comment:
# Find a user by its confirmation token and try to confirm it.
# If no user is found, returns a new user with an error.
# If the user is already confirmed, create an error for the user
# Options must have the confirmation_token

children.name: confirm
children.comment:
# Confirm a user by setting it's confirmed_at to actual time. If the user
# is already confirmed, add an error to email field. If the user is invalid
# add errors

children.name: pending_any_confirmation
children.comment: # Checks whether the record requires any confirmation.

children.name: unlock_strategy_enabled?
children.comment: # Is the unlock enabled for the given unlock strategy?

children.name: find_scope!
children.comment:
# Receives an object and find a scope for it. If a scope cannot be found,
# raises an error. If a symbol is given, it's considered to be the scope.

children.name: to
children.comment: # Gives the class the mapping points to.

children.name: modules
children.comment: # Return modules for the mapping.

children.name: stringify_params
children.comment: # Force keys to be string to avoid injection on mongoid related database.

children.name: devise_mail
children.comment: # Configure default email options

children.name: subject_for
children.comment:
# Set up a subject doing an I18n lookup. At first, it attempts to set a subject
# based on the current mapping:
#
#   en:
#     devise:
#       mailer:
#         confirmation_instructions:
#           user_subject: '...'
#
# If one does not exist, it fallbacks to ActionMailer default:
#
#   en:
#     devise:
#       mailer:
#         confirmation_instructions:
#           subject: '...'
#

children.name: devise_controller?
children.comment:
# Return true if it's a devise_controller. false to all controllers unless
# the controllers defined inside devise. Useful if you want to apply a before
# filter to all controllers, except the ones in devise:
#
#   before_action :my_filter, unless: :devise_controller?

children.name: warden
children.comment: # The main accessor for the warden proxy instance

children.name: valid?
children.comment: # A valid strategy for rememberable needs a remember token in the cookies.

children.name: mapping
children.comment: # Checks if a valid scope was given for devise and find mapping based on this scope.

children.name: mailer
children.comment: # Get the mailer class from the mailer reference object.

children.name: friendly_token
children.comment:
# Generate a friendly string randomly to be used as token.
# By default, length is 20 characters.

children.name: find_all
children.comment: # Normalizes the arguments and passes it on to find_templates.

children.name: call!
children.comment:
# The logic for dispatching any additional actions that need
# to be taken. For instance, calling the request phase if
# the request path is recognized.
#
# @param env [Hash] The Rack environment.

# Returns value of the key stored in the session or
# +nil+ if the given key is not found in the session.
# Returns the value of the cookie by +name+, or +nil+ if no such cookie exists.

children.name: pbkdf2_hmac
children.comment:
# OpenSSL::PKCS5.pbkdf2_hmac has been renamed to OpenSSL::KDF.pbkdf2_hmac.
# This method is provided for backwards compatibility.
